or in predominantly White contexts.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aAfrican American doctoral studentsxAttitudes. 0aAfrican American doctoral studentsxSocial conditions. 0aAfrican American universities and colleges. 0aAfrican AmericansxEducation (Graduate) 0aAfrican AmericansxEducation (Graduate). 0aAfrican AmericansxRace identity. 0aDoctoral studentsxAfrican AmericansxAttitudes. 0aDoctoral studentsxAfrican AmericansxSocial conditions. 0aUniversities and collegeszUnited StatesxGraduate work. 4aAfrican American Studies : African American Studies. 4aEducation : Education. 4aEducation : Higher Education. 4aGender and Sexuality : Gender Studies. 4aGender and Sexuality : Women's Studies. 7aEDUCATION / Higher.2bisacsh1 aBarker, Marco J., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFelder Small, Pamela, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGasman, Marybeth, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143847801240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438478012423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438478012/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles